Talks between China and Portugal on thefuture of Macao have ended and the two countries will issue ajoint statement at 5 P.M. Peking time (0900 GMT), PortugueseAmbassador Octavio Valerio said.    "We are very happy with the results," Valerio told reportersafter four days of discussions on how and when thePortuguese-run peninsula in southern China will be handed backto Peking. REUTER&#3;